      <p>The accuracy difference between the top and bottom tools is 3.9 percentage points. That may sound small, but at scale it is significant. For a 100,000-address list, the difference between 98.4% and 94.5% accuracy means 3,900 additional addresses misclassified. If those are false positives (invalid addresses classified as valid), they translate directly into bounces that damage your sender reputation.</p>

